1) login to deska-dev
2) su - postgres
3) users & roles:

postgres=# CREATE USER kundratj;
CREATE ROLE
postgres=# create user hubik;
CREATE ROLE
postgres=# create user krejcova;
CREATE ROLE
postgres=# create user kerpl;
CREATE ROLE
postgres=# create role deska_team;
CREATE ROLE
postgres=# grant deska_team to hubik, kerpl, krejcova, kundratj;
GRANT ROLE
postgres=# \du
                                 List of roles
 Role name  | Superuser | Create role | Create DB | Connections |  Member of
------------+-----------+-------------+-----------+-------------+--------------
 deska_team | no        | no          | no        | no limit    |
 hubik      | no        | no          | no        | no limit    | {deska_team}
 kerpl      | no        | no          | no        | no limit    | {deska_team}
 krejcova   | no        | no          | no        | no limit    | {deska_team}
 kundratj   | no        | no          | no        | no limit    | {deska_team}
 postgres   | yes       | yes         | yes       | no limit    |
(6 rows)
postgres=# create DATABASE deska_dev OWNER deska_team;
CREATE DATABASE


Stuff below was done as kundratj:
deska_dev=> create schema deska_dev authorization deska_team;
